{"Body":"<p>In WALS (World Atlas of Language Structures), \"Number of Cases\" is listed for most languages. However, this information is absent for Portuguese. </p>\n\n<p>Does Portuguese have any morphological case marking? If so, how many cases, and what sources could I cite for that?</p>\n", "Id":"1879", "LastEditorUserId":"899", "AcceptedAnswerId":"1881", "Title":"How many morphological cases does Portuguese have?", "CreationDate":"2012-05-05T17:14:10.057", "OwnerUserId":"899", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<morphology><reference-request><online-resources><portuguese><morphological-typology>", "AnswerCount":"1", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2012-05-05T17:53:24.410", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"3", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"899", "AccountId":"1369736", "Views":"4", "Reputation":"92", "CreationDate":"2012-04-05T04:34:23.227", "DisplayName":"Julie", "LastAccessDate":"2012-12-08T23:39:33.543"}, "ViewCount":"472", "LastActivityDate":"2012-05-05T20:19:37.880", "Score":"3", "CommentCount":"6", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"3", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"899", "AccountId":"1369736", "Views":"4", "Reputation":"92", "CreationDate":"2012-04-05T04:34:23.227", "DisplayName":"Julie", "LastAccessDate":"2012-12-08T23:39:33.543"}}